d-curves.md)  \n Defines antialiasing and how use antialiasing when drawing lines and curves.\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,305],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Lines, Curves, and Shapes\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"shapes [Windows Forms], filling\"\n  - \"splines [Windows Forms], drawing\"\n  - \"shapes. drawing\"\n  - \"lines [Windows Forms], drawing\"\n  - \"curves [Windows Forms], drawing\"\nms.assetid: ace6e8d4-4e94-486b-9681-758a6667dc7f","nodes":[{"content":"Lines, Curves, and Shapes","nodes":[{"pos":[0,25],"content":"Lines, Curves, and Shapes","nodes":[{"content":"Lines, Curves, and Shapes","pos":[0,25]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[312,337],"content":"Lines, Curves, and Shapes","linkify":"Lines, Curves, and Shapes","nodes":[{"content":"Lines, Curves, and Shapes","pos":[0,25]}]},{"pos":[338,501],"content":"The vector graphics portion of <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ndptecgdiplus](../../../../includes/ndptecgdiplus-md.md)]</ph> is used to draw lines, draw curves, and to draw and fill shapes.","source":"The vector graphics portion of [!INCLUDE[ndptecgdiplus](../../../../includes/ndptecgdiplus-md.md)] is used to draw lines, draw curves, and to draw and fill shapes."},{"pos":[510,525],"content":"In This Section","linkify":"In This Section","nodes":[{"content":"In This Section","pos":[0,15]}]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Vector Graphics Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](vector-graphics-overview.md)</ept>","pos":[529,584],"source":"[Vector Graphics Overview](vector-graphics-overview.md)"},{"content":"Discusses vector graphics.","pos":[588,614]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Pens, Lines, and Rectangles in GDI+<ept id=\"p1\">](pens-lines-and-rectangles-in-gdi.md)</ept>","pos":[621,695],"source":"[Pens, Lines, and Rectangles in GDI+](pens-lines-and-rectangles-in-gdi.md)"},{"content":"Discusses drawing lines and rectangles.","pos":[699,738]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Ellipses and Arcs in GDI+<